vaccines.refrigerationNotes: Must be stored and transported at −70ºC. It can be stored for up to 15 days in a thermal shipping box with dry ice. It can be kept for five days at standard refrigeration.
vaccines.description: Pfizer was the first company to report positive phase 3 clinical data. It plans to produce 50M doses in 2020 and 1.3B in 2021.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: Trial shows vaccine is more than 90% effective (later updated to 95%)

vaccines.refrigerationNotes: Normal fridge temperatures for 30 days. Long-term storage for up to six months requires −20ºC.
vaccines.description: Moderna and Pfizer both use a new vaccine approach involving messenger RNA. Moderna expects to have 20M doses for the U.S. in December and 100M globally in Q1.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: Application for emergency use with U.S. FDA

vaccines.description: AstraZeneca struck deals for 3 billion doses even before any late-stage study results. That's more than twice as many as any other candidate. Initial clinical results were mixed.

This small biotech firm has never brought a product to market. It received more than $1.6 billion from the U.S. and $399 million from the Coalition for Epidemic Preparedness. The stock rose 3,000% in nine months.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: 30,000-person trial in U.S. and Mexico opens for enrollment

vaccines.trialDetail: 60k enrolled in a trial of 1 dose. recently announced a 30k study using 2 doses—just in case
vaccines.description: Of the leading candidates, this is the easiest to distribute, requiring just one dose and standard refrigeration. To hedge its bets, J&J announced a separate trial with two doses in November.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: Trial size reduced to 40,000 people because of high Covid prevelence. Trial is full eight days later
Company expects results by end of January

vaccines.trialDetail: Sinovac has two late-stage candidates. CoronaVac has the global contracts. Two studies of 13k each, in Brazil and Turkey. Studies also planned for Indonesia
vaccines.refrigerationNotes: Standard Refrigeration (2–8ºC). Stable for up to 3 years.
vaccines.description: Sinovac's vaccine triggers an immune response using the Covid-19 virus itself, after it has been chemically inactivated.
A variation of the Russian vaccine, known as Sputnik V, can be stored using standard refrigeration temperatures of 2–8ºC. It’s currently available in limited quantities.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: Putin calls for mass vaccination using Sputnik V

vaccines.description: CanSino's shot was approved for the Chinese military even before late-stage tests began. It uses a harmless cold virus to deliver its genetic payload.

earlyApprovalEvents.eventText: Vaccine is cleared for Chinese military use

vaccines.description: Sinopharm administered hundreds of thousands of doses before its vaccine was fully tested.

trialEnrollmentEvents.eventText: China approves vaccine for general use after trial shows 79% efficacy
